Package: faSTM
Title: Fast Structural Topic Models (Rust Backend, Drop-in for 'stm')
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Neal", "Caren", email = "neal.caren@unc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A fast, drop-in fitting backend for structural topic models that
    returns an object compatible with the 'stm' package. faSTM fits the
    logistic-normal STM (with prevalence and content covariates) via the
    Rust core from 'topica', then hands the result back as an 'stm'-shaped
    S3 object so that stm's own labelTopics(), plot(), findThoughts(),
    sageLabels(), and toLDAvis() work unmodified. It also ships its own
    estimateEffect() implementing the method-of-composition (honest
    per-document posterior propagation). Text preparation is delegated to
    'stm' (textProcessor(), prepDocuments()). An opt-in stochastic
    variational ("svi") inference path scales fitting to large corpora.
